Now `ngx_posted_next_events` and `ngx_event_move_posted_next`:
This is a deferred-write optimization. When a connection's write buffer is full (NGX_AGAIN), instead of keeping it in the normal posted queue and retrying every loop, the event is moved to `ngx_posted_next_events`. At the start of the next loop, `ngx_event_move_posted_next` moves them back to `ngx_posted_events`, sets `ready=1` and `available=-1`, and forces timer=0 (no blocking). This defers the retry to the next iteration rather than spinning.

